Response to
Episode 1 - "Standing Up in the Milky Way" by Kevin Wang
@-------------------------------------------------
I really enjoyed the special effects used in the show, particularly the "ship of imagination", because our future spacecrafts might look like that and the journey that it goes through. I had known that the Universe has existed for a long time, but relating its age to a calendar and seeing that humans barely existed for seconds really put it in a new light. Relating to the size of the Universe, everyone knows about Copernicus and Kepler, but no one talks about Bruno, who really pushed the limits of the size of the Universe. On that note, I like how science is a cooperative discipline, in which generations build upon generations of knowledge. It is also hard to imagine how the moon was ten times brighter than it is now. Another mindblowing fact is that planets outnumber stars, which I still can't bring myself to believe.

Tyson said that imagination alone is not enough because the reality of nature is far more strange than anything we can imagine. I feel this is completely true, but it just makes me want to find out the answers to the mysteries. In addition, I like the idea of a multiverse. Whether or not we can test that theory, or even whether or not it's true, the idea is a cool one. Expect for the story of Bruno, most of the facts I more or less knew, so the question I have is how the special effects were made? What computer graphics methods were utilized?
