Response to
Episode 3 - "When Knowledge Conquered Fear"
@-------------------------------------------------
Humans like patterns, and want to find patterns to show that they are on earth for a reason.
-They saw the pattern of stars as a calendar, and knew when to migrate / what actinos to take to survive the coming season
-Civilizations all around the world saw comets as portents of doom because they did not follow the patterns that they observed in the stars, and freaked out whenever they saw a comet. It signaled that there would be famine, war, or pestilence. 
-It is important to challenge the norms set in place and to be curious, like Edmond Halley. Halley's curiousity led to him to eventually discover that comets follow a fixed orbit around the earth, and used mathematics to predict when a particular comet (Halley's comet) would reappear in the sky.  
-Halley also had the discernment to meet up with Isaac Newton, who had already discovered the laws of planetary motion but was hiding his proof. This shows the importance of changing up your approach to solving a problem, as Halley realized that his group consisting of Robert Hooke and Christopher Wren was not working. 
